  "prompt": "Is there any management quota at PCCOE Pune? What are the fees?",
  "response": "Pimpri Chinchwad College of Engineering (PCCOE) in Pune, like many engineering colleges in India, may have a management quota as part of its admissions process. Management quotas are typically reserved seats that allow institutions to admit students based on criteria other than the central or state-level entrance exams, such as JEE Main or MHT-CET. These seats often provide an opportunity for students who may have not secured admission through the regular merit-based process.\n\nThe fees for management quota seats can be significantly higher than the regular tuition fees for merit-based admissions. The exact fee structure for management quota seats at PCCOE or any other institution can vary each year based on university guidelines and management decisions.\n\nFor accurate and up-to-date information regarding the availability of management quota seats and the specific fees involved, it is advisable to directly contact the admissions office of PCCOE or visit their official website. They will provide the most reliable details concerning admissions and fee structures for the current academic year.",
